'''Charles Upton''' (born December 13, 1948) is an American [[poet]] and metaphysician.<ref>http://www.bookrags.com/biography/charles-upton-dlb/</ref>

==Life==
Born in [[San Francisco]], Charles Upton grew up in [[Marin County, California]].  He attended [[Catholic]] schools through high school. He attended [[University of California Davis|UC Davis]] for  four days.

==Career==
In San Francisco, he met the poet [[Lew Welch]], who became his mentor. Although much younger than most of the Beat poets, Upton's first two volumes of poetry were also published by [[City Lights Bookstore|City Lights]].  It was associated with many of the earlier Beat poets.

After his first two volumes of poems were published, Upton became involved with the [[Sanctuary Movement]] for [[Central American]] [[refugees]]. He produced and distributed a video, ''Through the Needle’s Eye'', containing testimonies of refugees.

In the late 1980s he was briefly involved with the "magical populism" of the [[New Age]] peace movement.  He studied group [[dreamwork]] and dream networking.

In 1988 he joined a traditional [[Sufi]] order.  Under his wife's influence, Upton became interested in the [[metaphysics]] of the [[Traditionalist School|Traditionalist]] or Perennialist School (the followers of [[Rene Guenon]], [[Ananda Coomaraswamy]] and [[Frithjof Schuon]]).  He continues to be partly identified with this school.

His papers are held at [[University of Connecticut]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/findaids/Upton/MSS20030017.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-11-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090801085905/http://doddcenter.uconn.edu/findaids/Upton/MSS20030017.html |archivedate=August 1, 2009 |df=mdy }}</ref>

==Activism==
Charles Upton conceived of The Covenants Initiative which urges Muslims to abide by the covenants concluded between Muhammad and the Christian communities of his time.<ref>http://weku.fm/post/islamic-scholar-speaks-muslim-covenant</ref> The Covenants Initiative has now expanded into the Genocide Initiative. This new effort, created upon the request of Bishop Francis Kalabat from the Chaldean Catholic Church, seeks to place pressure on political players to describe the crimes of ISIS and other Takfiri terrorists as acts of cultural, religious, and ethnic genocide.

==Marriage and family==
He married [[Jennifer Doane]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.seriousseekers.com/Teachers%20and%20Contributors/teachers_priority_1_traditionalandfriends/teachers_contributors_Upton_c.htm# |title=Archived copy |access-date=November 16, 2009 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080821133344/http://seriousseekers.com/Teachers%20and%20Contributors/teachers_priority_1_traditionalandfriends/teachers_contributors_Upton_c.htm# |archive-date=August 21, 2008 |dead-url=yes |df=mdy-all }}</ref>  After living in [[Marin County, California]], they currently live in [[Lexington, Kentucky]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sophiaperennis.com/shop/perennis/21.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2009-11-16 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100524082201/http://www.sophiaperennis.com/shop/perennis/21.html |archivedate=May 24, 2010 |df=mdy }}</ref>

