[[File:Eschinardi - Microcosmi physicomathematici, 1658 - 882578.jpg |thumb|''Microcosmi physicomathematici'', 1658]]


'''Francesco Eschinardi''' (13 December 1623 - 12 January 1703) was an [[Italy|Italian]] [[mathematician]] and [[philosopher]]<ref>{{cite web|url= https://thesaurus.cerl.org/cgi-bin/record.pl?rid=cnp01389635|title= Eschinardi, Francesco (1623-1703) in CERL Thesaurus}}</ref>.

== Life ==

Eschinardi was born in [[Rome]]. From 1637 he studied [[mathematics]], [[philosophy]], [[logic]] and [[rhetoric]] at the [[Society of Jesus]] school. He worked as professor at the [[Roman College]] and was a member of the [[Pontifical Academy of Sciences]] from 1679<ref>{{cite book|url=http://www.treccani.it/enciclopedia/francesco-eschinardi_(Dizionario-Biografico)//|title= Eschinardi, Francesco|work=Dizionario Biografico degli Italiani|publisher=Treccani|volume=43|year=1993}}</ref>.  

