{{Orphan|date=June 2016}}
'''Karsten Friis Johansen''' (5 December 1930 – 29 July 2010) was a [[Denmark|Danish]] [[philosophy|philosopher]] and [[classical philology|classical philologist]].
He was a brother of [[Holger Friis Johansen]]. He was a librarian at the [[Royal Library, Denmark]] from 1957 to 1968, took the [[dr.phil.]] degree with the thesis ''Studier over Platons Parmenides'' in 1964 and was a professor of antique and medieval philosophy at the [[University of Copenhagen]] from 1969 to 1998.<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|url=http://www.denstoredanske.dk/Sprog,_religion_og_filosofi/Filosofi/Filosofi_og_filosoffer_-_1900-t./Filosoffer_1900-t._-_Norden_-_biografier/Karsten_Friis_Johansen|title=Karsten Friis Johansen|encyclopedia=[[Store Danske Encyklopædi]]|language=Danish|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref> He was a fellow of the [[Royal Danish Academy of Sciences and Letters]], [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]] and the [[Society for Danish Language and Literature]]. He also chaired ''Platonselskabet'' and ''Den Arnamagnæanske Stiftelse'' and was the secretary of ''Selskabet til Historisk Kildeskrifters Oversættelser''.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kristeligt-dagblad.dk/mennesker/d%C3%B8de-1216|title=Døde|date=17 August 2010|work=Kristeligt Dagblad|language=Danish|accessdate=12 January 2015}}</ref>
